	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I use some 64kb EEPROMs. They work great, but Flash is better. EEPROMs need an erasing step, Flash don't.
<br />
<br />AFAIK, Vcc is the working voltage, the same as +5V, for the NES. Vpp is the programming voltage, used by EPROMs. I can't really describe what GND is. The "Axx" pins are the ADDRESS pins, one for each bit. And "Dxx" are the DATA pins, also one for each bit.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


